        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>reedpipes with double reed: with conical bore [300195247], reedpipes with double reed [300205170], reedpipes (confined aerophones) [300042558], reeds (aerophones) [300193013], aerophones [300041622], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Use generally for reedpipes with double reed and conical bore. May also be used specifically for those reedpipes with double reed played in Western orchestral, chamber, and solo music.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Usese genéricamente para tubos de lengüeta con lengüeta doble y diámetro interior cónico. Puede también usarse específicamente para aquellos tubos de lengüeta doble que se usan para interpretar música occidental orquestal y de cámara, y para solos instrumentales.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Algemeen te gebruiken voor rietinstrumenten met een dubbel riet en conische boring. Meer specifiek: dubbelrietinstrumenten in westerse orkest- kamer- en solomuziek.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
